caption: Best Indian food in Chicago and nicest staff! My family has tried nearly every item on the menu and it's always great.  Best Gobi Manchurian! Ask to make things mild for your young child and they'll enjoy it too!
Decent food.

Incredible masala sauce at this place, good portions and the staff is super nice.

My dear American friends, before you get to any Indian food place, understand the difference between. chicken tikka and chicken tandoori. This place, puts tandoori chicken pieces (with red color) in a sweet and spicy sauce. And they call it chicken tikka masala. There is is no dish as chicken tandoori masala.

Worst experience ever! Waited inside their restaurant for *two* hours for my order, with a crowd of about 10-15 people who variously complained or gave up after waiting 1-2+ hours for their orders. Not only did they definitely violate COVID guidelines for indoor capacity but their poor customer service angered every customer (and delivery driver) for having to wait 1-2+ hours (or just gave up and never came back). A crowd riot almost broke out because people were so upset.

The chicken Beriany is top quality along with the veggie mamausa. A must try people reading this post. The sauce is quality as well, the nam is great.  I encourage the owners to continue with fresh food, don't be cheap, this is a top notch excellent food ...
Masala Tea was good
Got their food to-go and service wise, it was excellent. Well packaged and prepared. I got their chicken tikka masala and samosas. The chicken tikka was not that good, i've had better

Really poor customer service — we placed an order a bit after 7pm on a Saturday evening, and it took over two hours  for them to get to our order.  When we call to inquire, they do not pick up.  I finally managed to get ahold of a live person at 9pm, and was told they have just gotten to our order.  I get that Saturday is a busy time, but when we are told it’s a 1 hour wait, and then it becomes a two hour wait, maybe your staff could understand why we’re a bit irked and know that “we’re busy” doesn’t quite suffice.  Glad you’re “busy” enough that losing customers doesn’t really matter.

I ordered from grubhub and it never arrived. I called the restaurant 10 mins after the max waiting time and they said the food was 5 mins from being done. Now it's been almost two hours and I called them to check on the status. The person on the phone insisted it'll be delivered and then threw out 10 more minutes. We asked to cancel and she rudely hung up on us. So disappointing as I was looking forward to this meal.

Plates are great size to share. My boyfriend and I came in earlier today and we were absolutely famished! We stumbled upon this cute restaurant sweetly placed in the middle of this shopping center around the corner from Lincoln park, and my my my...were we impressed. Not only was the service excellent our server was so sweet she was witty and very accommodating. Definitely hostess with the mostess!!! Butter chicken and rice came out in top speed and the flavor was superb! It was above mild spicy but enough to get that zing We was looking for but still maintains all flavor. Nan was definitely freshhhhh! Will come back when we make our way back to Chicago, but until the head on in it’s a great spot to kick back and enjoy the taste of India !!

Fantastic restaurant and one of the best Indian restaurants in Chicago, portion sizes are awesome, and every time I’ve ordered takeout it’s always tasted amazing definitely recommend for anyone interested in Indian cuisine.
I've recently moved to this area, and I've already stopped here for dinner...twice! The food is incredible, the portions are generous, and the people are kind. Lincoln Park is lucky to have Rangoli!

Our new favorite go-to Indian restaurant. The food is amazing and the staff couldn't be better!

This place was great. Huge portions too. We ordered: gobi manchurian butter chicken lamb rogan josh chana masala chicken haryali chicken tikka masala veggie samosas coconut rice chili and garlic naan butter naan We ordered takeout for a group of 4, but this could have fed a group of 8-10, the portions are so generous. Reasonably priced too. The gobi was alright, the butter chicken, lamb, and tikka masala were amazing, and we really liked everything else. The chicken in the haryali was slightly dry/tough. Samosas were goooood. The naan was pretty standard. I'd skip the coconut rice next time. I will definitely be back!!!!!!
Nice environment and super amiable service. The meals were crisp and enchanting. Will easily recommend this spot to friends. Convenient rates and generous meals. Keep up the great work.

We ordered from the Rangoli website, which sent the order to the Wicker Park location instead of the Lincoln Park location. We didn’t know this until we got to the Lincoln Park location, but the staff was incredibly nice and told us they’d remake our order right away since we had already paid online. Great service! Also the food was to die for (Butter Chicken and Paneer Better Masala). If you’re going to get Indian food in Chicago, go here!
This spot provides superb service as well as delightful menu. The best spot in the area. The meals came out quickly and the prices are reasonable. Highly recommended.
Delicious,  servers very nice. Sunday buffet!

The food is great and the staff/hostess are always really welcoming. Have been here 3 times and will continue to go back!

At the first moment  you enter this place  the personel give you an excellent feeling. Very warm waiters, it is a friendly restaurant to hang out with friends and colleagues or with your date. Excellent  meals, experienced  chief cook and stuff, comfortable  price and professional  service. Highly recommended.

Pretty much everything we ordered was good. Starters - Onion bhajhee, Entree - Veg Vindaloo and Tadka daal together with bread - Paneer Kulcha and Onion Kulcha..

I ended up going here with my Meetup group since our event ended early and we were hungry. The staff was very friendly when we arrived and sat us immediately. They had a lunch buffet special so we all decided to try that to sample the food. I had the lamb curry, chicken curry, chana masala, palak paneer, samosa, and rice for the main course. I usually don't eat a lot of lamb but I liked how it was made here. They brought us naan bread as well. I wish I could have tried their other naan bread because there was a variety of them on the non-buffet menu.  Overall I think the curries could have been spicier but there was enough of a slow heat that built up with time. The temperature of the food could have been a tad warmer but it was a buffet so that's kind of expected. For dessert, I had both the rice pudding and double ka meetha. I never had these desserts in this fashion before and I was very pleased with them. For my group the double ka meetha stole the show. Some even went back for thirds. The staff was attentive in making sure we had enough water and other drinks. I would like to try this place again when I'm by Lincoln Park Zoo. It wasn't that far of a walk from there.

Very attentive staff and food tastes very fresh. Refreshing to have an authentic lunch buffet that is in the area, and we don't have to travel to Devon Ave. Also, the price for the lunch buffet is great at around $13 or $14 on weekdays.
Cozy yet modern Indian restaurant. The food was great and so was the service. Will def return!

At the first moment  you enter that restaurant  the stuff gives you an excellent feeling. Very courteous hosts, it is a kind restaurant to  pass time with friends or with your date. yummy  meals, talented  chef, modest  cost and courteous  service. Warmly recommended.

Great food and very good service by Adithya. Been to this place earlier as well and very receptive waiters. Samosas and mango Kulfi are my favourites! Buffet can have more vegetarian options.

I eat in this spot a lot since I work nearby. I love how their service is always great and they keep the spot clean all the time. Rates are affordable and they serve large portions.

- The pav bhaji had virtually no tomato and was much thicker and less savory than it should be - The navratan korma had undercooked peas - The bagara baingan had almost no flavor or spice - The servers didn't really engage with us or ask our opinions on the food, nor did they make an attempt to rectify the situation after we told them that the pav bhaji was bad.

The food is good, the service prompt and courteous, but their portions are a bit small, especially for the entrées at their price point.

The food here was truly excellent. Out of the appetizers, the Gobi Manchurian, samosas, and fried onions were all excellent. Among the sides, the chili and garlic naan and coconut rice were phenomenal, and while the raita was more liquid than expected it was still very good. For dinner, the Madras chicken korma was very tender and had a good amount of spice. The rasmalai for dessert was very sweet, so I would recommend chai to go with it. The staff were very friendly and accommodating, everything was prepared in a good amount of time. It's not especially cheap (about $18 for an entree and rice), but it's worth the cost.
Not as Dope as Rangoli Classic Indian Dining, however really good classic Indian fare

The food was excellent. The restaurant uses a stone tandoori oven to bake the naan and meats which imparts great flavor. The tandoori chicken was great.  The rogan josh was also very flavorful. It's  Byob but there's  a  liquor store conviently located two doors down.

Finally a really good Indian restaurant in Lincoln Park! Delicious food and  really interesting green chicken curry dish based on cilantro with some heat. Naan was perfect (this is very important to me!).  Only flaw was that service was struggling to keep up once things got really busy.
